# CPSC recalls chat — formatting and UX

## Backend (`backend/services/llm/rag_chain.py`)

- **`SYSTEM_PROMPT`**: Instruct the model to answer in **GitHub-flavored Markdown** readable in a chat bubble.
- **Lists**: Put a **blank line** before the first numbered item and **after** the intro sentence (e.g. `...retailer:\n\n1.` — never `...retailer:1.`).
- **Each recall**: Use a numbered block with **blank lines between** items; inside each item use `**Label:** value` on separate lines where helpful.
- **Facts**: Use `recall_number`, dates, and URLs from the provided context only; avoid placeholder text like "Not specified" when the context omits a field — say it is not listed instead.
- **Links**: `[short label](https://...)`; keep one primary link per recall (e.g. CPSC recall page).

## Frontend (`frontend/src/app/chat/**`, `frontend/src/lib/api.ts`)

- Assistant bubbles use **`ChatMarkdown`** (`react-markdown` + `remark-gfm` + `rehype-sanitize` in `frontend/src/components/ChatMarkdown.tsx`) for both **streaming** and **saved** messages. User bubbles stay plain text.
- External links (`http`/`https`): `target="_blank"` and `rel="noopener noreferrer"`.

## SSE (`frontend/src/lib/api.ts`)

- Call **`onDone` only when `currentEvent === "done"`**. Empty `data:` lines must not finalize the stream (avoids duplicate assistant messages).

